This paper deals with sketching and estimating the Jaccard index, which is a common problem in database systems and data mining. Therefore, cs.DB (Databases) is the most likely category. The paper also introduces a new probabilistic sketch, which involves data structures and algorithms, making cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) another likely category. The sketch also involves information theory, specifically the HyperLogLog count-distinct sketch, which makes cs.IT (Information Theory) a possible category. The paper also discusses the trade-off between space and accuracy, which is a common theme in machine learning and statistics, making cs.LG (Machine Learning) a possible category. Finally, the paper involves probabilistic algorithms and analysis, which is a common theme in cs.DM (Discrete Mathematics).
